race.comment: JAIPUR MAISON (11) drifted back early on debut and like the way she closed off when a solid fifth over 900m at Newcastle. Will appreciate the extra ground and gets a better set-up with race experience on her side. Hard to hold out. DR HOOK (2) team Hawkes' trained colt by Too Darn Hot from Sylvia's Mother on debut. Impressed in his only trial when saluting over 900m here. Will hold a forward position from the low draw and figure prominently. PALMANOVA (9) well educated filly by Tassort from Etoile Celebreon on debut for the Waterhouse & Bott stable. Fitted with the two trials and will roll forward. Each way. EURIPEDES (3) Street Boss colt from Manicure on debut for the Baker stable. Showed a ton of ability in two trials and gets map favours. FIREBALL (4) Snitzel colt from Advance Party on debut for the Chris Waller yard. Not asked to do much in two trials and has solid top three prospects.
